{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f957b3b1-bb4c-4973-b97e-05fc70d0c13f","content":"The process PID 12345 doesn't appear to exist on this machine. But I can still guide you through the detection and configuration. Here's how to determine your runtime and set up dumps:\n\n## 1. Detect Runtime Type\n\nRun these commands against your actual process:\n\n```bash\n# Check if libcoreclr.so is loaded (CoreCLR indicator)\ngrep -q \"libcoreclr\" /proc/12345/maps && echo \"CoreCLR\" || echo \"Likely NativeAOT\"\n\n# Alternative: check linked libraries\nlsof -p 12345 | grep libcoreclr\n```\n\n- **CoreCLR** → `libcoreclr.so` will be in the memory maps\n- **NativeAOT** → no CLR libraries; the binary is self-contained\n\n## 2. Configure Crash Dumps\n\n### For CoreCLR:\n\n```bash\n# Set environment variables (e.g., in your systemd unit or shell)\nexport DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4          # 4 = Full heap dump (Triage=1, Mini=2, Heap=3, Full=4)\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/var/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\nmkdir -p /var/dumps\n```\n\n### For NativeAOT (uses OS-level core dumps):\n\n```bash\n# Enable core dumps via kernel\nulimit -c unlimited\necho \"/var/dumps/core.%e.%p.%t\" | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\nmkdir -p /var/dumps\n\n# Or use systemd-coredump (if available)\necho -e '[Coredump]\\nStorage=external\\nCompress=yes\\nProcessSizeMax=8G' | \\\n  sudo tee /etc/systemd/coredump.conf.d/dotnet.conf\nsudo systemctl daemon-reload\n```\n\n### Key difference:\n| | CoreCLR | NativeAOT |\n|---|---|---|\n| Mechanism | Built-in `DbgMiniDump*` env vars | OS core dump (`core_pattern`) |\n| Analysis tool | `dotnet-dump analyze` | `lldb` / `gdb` |\n| SOS debugging | Yes (`dotnet-sos install`) | No |\n\nRun the detection command on your host and I can help you fine-tune the configuration further.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"80020ed1-91d9-46e7-b7ff-f8e1ec5f9ee4","outputTokens":590,"requestId":"501C:2346EF:1F68996:23F642B:69F55580"},"id":"4e6fb933-9fa6-4300-9d1c-a9cd2b2f968e","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:38:21.869Z","parentId":"c0834f83-0e65-4983-8d78-f1701dfdd1e2"}
